lowing{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/myronmarston/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2010-09-01T23:30:26Z","updated_at":"2010-09-01T23:30:26Z","body":"I just pushed a fix [here](http://github.com/myronmarston/rspec-core/commits/issue_129/).\n\nNote that I'm not 100% sure of the repurcussions of my change.  Before the change, my specs were being run using a command like:\n\n<pre>\n/Users/mmarston/.rvm/rubies/ruby-1.8.7-p249/bin/ruby -S  /Users/mmarston/.rvm/rubies/ruby-1.8.7-p249/bin/ruby  -Ilib -Ispec \"spec/nulldb_spec.rb\"\n</pre>\n\n\nWith my commit, the command is now:\n\n<pre>\n/Users/mmarston/.rvm/rubies/ruby-1.8.7-p249/bin/ruby -S  -Ilib -Ispec \"spec/nulldb_spec.rb\"\n</pre>\n\n\nThe path to the ruby interpretter (the argument after `-S`) was the problem; removing it fixed my specs.  But I'm not sure why it was there in the first place--why do you need to give the ruby interpreter a path to itself?  So I'm a bit mystified as to why it was there in the first place, and this may break something I'm not aware of (all specs pass, though).\n\nDavid: in the past you've requested that we use issues rather than pull requests to submit patches.  With github's new pull request system, would you like us to start using that?\n\nMyron\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/384155/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eye